{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"## Self code-review (2 finder agents + verify) — remediated 4 findings\n\nRan a correctness pass + a robustness/security pass on the staged diff. Cleared as safe\n(verified, not bugs): set -e + `return 1` on sha-mismatch still aborts; `cut -d= -f2-`\nhandles `=` in values; the `type = OAUTH` grep is anchored so it never matches a comment;\ncross-file var names all align. Real findings fixed:\n\n1. **secure.config clobber (correctness).** `cat > secure.config` truncated the file every\n   boot, dropping Gerrit's own keys (registerEmailPrivateKey, etc.). FIX: write both creds\n   with `git config --file` — a MERGE (Gerrit configs ARE git-config files). Verified a\n   pre-existing key survives.\n2. **Value-metachar hazard (correctness).** sed client-id substitution + unquoted heredoc\n   secret could mangle values containing | & $ ` \\. FIX: `git config --file` set is\n   metachar-immune. Verified: id `0v23li&weird|id` and secret `se$cret`+backtick+`\\back&|`\n   round-trip byte-exact.\n3. **Unconditional OAuth requirement (both agents).** fetch-secrets.sh hard-required the\n   OAuth creds on every boot → non-OAUTH rollback-via-compose-up broke; fresh apply died.\n   FIX: fetch them via get_param_optional (blank if unpopulated); compose-up's OAUTH branch\n   enforces presence only when auth.type = OAUTH is actually selected.\n4. **compose-up ↔ install-plugins coupling + moving-artifact time-bomb (robustness).**\n   compose-up called install-plugins.sh (network) on every boot, coupling whole-stack\n   availability to GerritForge CI and the non-boot-critical events-log. FIX: install-plugins\n   is a separate operator step (runbook Step 3); compose-up only VERIFIES oauth.jar present\n   (fail-loud). Also reverted the user_data.sh change — those params have NO cloud-init\n   consumer (containers read infra/compose/.env, not /etc/rebar/.env), so adv-15 was a\n   conditional false positive; adding them only created a fresh-boot FATAL.\n\nPlus: chmod 600 re-asserted on secure.config; `git` host-prereq guard in compose-up;\nrunbook Step 2 recommends create-CHANGEME-then-overwrite to avoid mid-apply\nParameterAlreadyExists. shellcheck + make lint clean; materialization functionally tested."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782931552480483001,"uuid":"6dd55dcc-74bb-4677-a87f-4891b813d6d1"}